.DT
cast
Discworld player help
cast

.SH Name
.SI 5
cast - Spell casting
.EI

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
cast <spell> [from <scroll>] [at|on <target|targets>]
     [using <components>] [with <argument>]
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
Cast is used when you want to activate a spell that you have learnt,
been taught or found in a scroll on your adventures.  You must use cast
followed by the spell you wish to cast followed by any information that is
appropriate to the spell.

Remember that priests must use the command 'perform' for rituals.
.EP

.SH Example
.SI 5
> cast light
The world lights up as you cast your spell.
> cast bees on lanfear using 3 dollops of honey
Lanfear looks really excited about the gift of honey.
.EI

.SH See also
.SI 5
spells
.EI
